Signals that are overhyped and should be excluded or demoted: Product launches and rebrands (mostly marcomms, not IC or Corp Comms). Trade press mentions as a trigger (everyone watches PRWeek; it is confirmation, not alpha). Earnings-call sentiment (beloved of quant funds but too noisy for a comms-hire trigger). Awards wins (counterintuitively a negative indicator \'97 employers use awards to justify retention bonuses, locking in the recipient for 6\'9612 months).\
\
The key design insight is signal stacking. No single signal has better than ~30% precision for predicting a specific comms hire; combining two or three independent signals (for example: HR1 filing plus no visible Head of IC on LinkedIn plus a Staffbase customer-story tag in the last year plus a CHRO change six months ago) pushes compound probability above 70%. This is precisely the cross-referencing work that Claude Code does better than any SaaS tool because it can hold all the signal streams in one context and reason over them.\
