The candidate-side signal universe: what actually predicts a move\
The research here yielded a counter-intuitive but important empirical finding. VMA Group's own Inside Insight research found that 82% of UK internal communicators are "at least open" to a move in the next 12 months, \
Vmagroup\
 and 58% are actively looking \
Vmagroup\
 (VMA Inside Insight 2017, reaffirmed in the 2024 edition). The 3Search 2025 survey of ~1,300 UK comms professionals put intent-to-search at 70% for the year. This changes the problem entirely: Sara's intelligence task is not "who is open to moving" \'97 almost everyone is \'97 but "who is moving in the next eight weeks, and what is the trigger I can act on".\
\
Against that baseline, only five candidate signals have genuine predictive value, and the rest are either noise or confirmation-only:\
\
LinkedIn's "Open to Work" flag, recruiter-visible view, via Sara's Sales Navigator Recruiter licence. This is self-declared timing intent. LinkedIn's own data shows Open-to-Work members receive approximately 2\'d7 InMails \
Qureos\
 and have a 53% response rate against 35% for non-flagged. \
Talentgroups\
 At \'a380k+ levels the public green-frame variant is rare; the recruiter-only variant is the dominant signal. Saved searches should be restricted to IC/Corp Comms titles, UK location, with tenure-in-role \uc0\u8805 18 months as a noise filter.\
Interim contract-end proximity, by Companies House cross-reference. For Sara's zero-to-24 interim target, this is the single most valuable candidate signal. Most interim communicators run personal service companies; their directorships, PSC records and filing histories are fully public on Companies House. Combined with LinkedIn current-role start dates and typical 6/9/12-month contract lengths, a simple T-minus-eight-weeks flag produces high-quality "about to be available" leads. LinkedIn activity uptick (posting frequency doubling against a trailing six-month baseline) is the confirmatory trigger. This is legally clean, lawful under UK GDPR legitimate-interests basis, and essentially invisible to every generalist sourcing tool on the market.\
Composite LinkedIn profile-refresh clustering. A single edit is noise; three or more edits across headline, About section, skills, photo, banner and featured section within a rolling 30-day window is the signal. This pattern is what Proxycurl (until its shutdown) and Coresignal detect via re-scrape diffs. For ongoing access, Bright Data's LinkedIn dataset at ~$0.001/record \
Proxycurl\
 is the licensed alternative.\
Personal-brand ignition clusters. Defined as any two of: Substack or personal-website launch; podcast-guest appearance in the last 60 days; posting-cadence at least double baseline; new byline in HBR, MIT Sloan, PRWeek or Raconteur; new speaker-bureau listing. Senior comms professionals systematically build visibility three to six months before a visible move to a NED/portfolio/CCO role or a consultancy launch. The cluster predicts; any single element does not.\
Removal of employer from headline or banner \'97 rare, but when it happens, it is high-confidence.\
