Tenure in role is not a trigger but a gate: at 2.5 to 4 years in a mid-senior UK IC role, the base-rate probability of movement within 12 months is elevated enough to warrant inclusion in downstream scoring, but using tenure alone as an alert would drown Sara in false positives given the 82% "at least open" baseline.\
