The eight ingestion sub-agents, running in parallel, cover: (1) Companies House Streaming on officer-change events filtered to CEO/CHRO/CPO/MD at target and lookalike companies; (2) HR1 redundancy feed from ONS plus the maintained FOI list; (3) IC platform customer-story scraper covering Staffbase, Poppulo, Firstup, SocialChorus case-study pages weekly; (4) RNS announcement filter via Investegate for Rule 2.7, ITF, TR-1, Capital Markets Day and Board Change types; (5) Regulator enforcement scraper covering FCA final notices, CMA cases, ICO data security register, Ofcom enforcement; (6) Job-ad cluster detector watching target-account careers pages and LinkedIn Jobs for comms-adjacent role density; (7) Trade press digest ingesting PRWeek Movers and Shakers, In.Comms, PRovoke, Communicate and CorpComms RSS feeds; (8) Candidate-side refresh detector consuming Bright Data's LinkedIn dataset for tenure-in-role, profile-refresh-cluster and Open-to-Work flags across a maintained watchlist of approximately 1,500 UK senior IC/Corp Comms professionals plus the 100 lapsed contacts. Each returns \uc0\u8804 2,000 tokens of structured JSON.\
\
The orchestrator then executes four pieces of cross-referencing logic that no off-the-shelf tool does. First, signal stacking: combining two or more independent signals against the same company multiplies the confidence score \'97 HR1 plus CHRO change plus Staffbase customer-story plus no current Head of IC on LinkedIn is a near-certain lead. Second, watchlist intersection: any signal touching Sara's 20\'9625 key accounts or 100 lapsed contacts is promoted to the top tier regardless of absolute score. Third, incumbent-to-candidate flip: when a senior comms leader appears in a "departure" signal (PRWeek move, LinkedIn tenure ended, Companies House officer filing), the orchestrator automatically checks the candidate-side memory store and flags the person both as a new BD lead (because their old employer now has a vacancy) and a new candidate lead (because they are likely now available \'97 often in transit between roles). Fourth, referral-chain tracking: when a placed candidate changes employer in the open record, the new employer becomes a warm-intro BD opportunity and the old employer a backfill candidate opportunity. This validates the sixth of the six prior-session gaps and is materially novel against the competitor set.\
\
Delivery is via Resend MCP (resend-mcp, Resend's official server) to Sara's inbox at approximately 07:15, with a short Slack notification containing the headline count. The full HTML body, markdown source and a separate JSON log are committed to a claude/briefs/YYYY-MM-DD branch in the repository, giving Sara an audit trail and letting her grep her own history (e.g., "did I already flag this lead in the last fortnight?") via a second Claude Code command.\
\
Guardrails: a PreToolUse hook blocks any Bash command touching rm, .env files, or paths outside state/ and briefs/; --max-budget-usd 1.50 per run is hard-capped; network egress is allowlisted to the explicit source domains plus Resend; LinkedIn direct scraping is explicitly blocked at the tool layer, forcing all LinkedIn signals through the Bright Data MCP licensed route.\
