\f0\fs26 \cf7 \cb5 1. The 7am cadence is wrong for a speed-sensitive market.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb5 Most high-value signals break during UK business hours. An RNS announcement at 10am, a Companies House officer filing at 2pm, a PRWeek breaking story at 4pm \'97 all sit in the queue until 7am tomorrow. In the April 2026 cold market, being 14\'9620 hours late on a CEO departure is the difference between first call and fifth call. A laser-focused commission tool needs a\'a0real-time alert surface\'a0for HIGH-confidence signal stacks during business hours, not just a morning digest.\cb1 \
\cb5 2. The tool only serves the planning moment \'97 not the commercial moments.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb5 Commission is won or lost in four specific conversations: pitching for retained, negotiating fee, submitting a candidate, and responding to a brief inside 72 hours. The spec I gave you serves none of them directly. A commission-maximised tool adds\'a0on-demand execution surfaces\'a0invoked at the moment of commercial truth:\cb1 \
